node.text: Throwback Thursday. A year ago today, I was working on a pilot about the Brides of Dracula with my fave partner-in-crime @maggiekiley.director. Starring the Queen of All Things @iamginatorres as Cleopatra. And @goran_visnjic as the suavest of Counts. And @erinrrichards as the saucy Madame de Sade. And @k8r3is as sweet, innocent Lily. Like so many other projects, we were shut down by the virus. A year later, the ladies haven’t seen the light of day…yet. But here’s a taste of the delicious, vampy fun we were working on…🔥👰🏽👰🏻👰🏼🧛🏻‍♂️🩸🖤💰🎭⭐️👀💥 📺

node.text: We truly saved the best...and scariest...for last. So much love for this cast, crew, writers, and fandom. Part Four finds our witches and mortals facing off against the Eldritch Terrors. And, friends, there will be monsters, sacrifices, last kisses, a satanic battle-of-the-bands, and some very, very special guest stars...before the most epic ending EVER. You are cordially invited to the End of All Things on December 31st, 2020. 🔮🖤🎢🌪⌛️🔥

node.text: If you haven’t watched #KatyKeene, #Riverdale’s sister-show, all episodes are available for streaming on #HBO Max starting midnight tonight!! There is so much HEART in this show--and lots of hearts, too! It’s a romantic-musical-comedy-drama-fairytale-dream set and filmed in the real NYC!! Love these actors, led by @lucyhale and @iamamurray, love this crew, and love these writers and editors. Settle into a warm bubble bath--or blow a few bubbles with your hand soap--and start binging!!! ❤️💋💃🏻👠🧨🍒👗📺👨🏻‍💻🏆

node.text: This came up on a FB feed today. Brought back so many memories. Two genius icons making magic. If you can find the entire Christmas special online. Watch it!!! It is the perfect way to get into the holiday spirit. 🎄💎⭐️⛄️🔥

node.text: “Come in from the rain. We’ve been expecting you.” An all-new, all-creepy #Riverdale premieres this Wednesday night on @thecw. It’s one of our semi-annual triptych episodes, written by Renaissance man @jamesdewille and moodily directed by David Lynch protege @madchenamick. Big things happen this week…🕷👠⛪️🎢🚢💨⚓️🎭🎟🎨🍔🔥🥀🐍⌛️☠️

node.text: Forces are gathering for the ultimate battle between Good and Evil as the cameras begin to roll on #Riverdale Season Six. But who will stand on which side? And who will live, and who will die? Everything has been a prelude to this. 🔥🌪🍔⌛️☠️💍👠👨🏼‍🤝‍👨🏽🎰🎢🚧🚑🎭🥩👭🏽👼🏽🦸🏻‍♂️💄💋💰💎⚰️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Roberto Aguirre-Sacasa on August 27, 2021 tagging @gsacasa, and @senchrisdodd. May be an image of 3 people, people standing and text that says '#FREEFRANCISCO !LIBERTAD YA! 30 DÍAS SIN SABER NADA #PresosPorQué'.

node.text: It’s been thirty days since my father was abducted and disappeared by the Ortega/Murillo regime in Nicaragua. In that time, we’ve had zero contact with him, nor spoken to anyone who has had direct contact with him. We know nothing about the conditions he’s being kept in—except that they’re extreme—nor his health. (He’s 76 and being denied medicine.) Other political prisoners have been missing more than a hundred days. Their families have also heard nothing. Worry is turning to despair. Horrible atrocities are happening every day, all over the world. What’s happening in Nicaragua to those who stand for freedom and democracy is one of them. Free the prisoners. Return them to their families. #freefrancisco #sosnicaragua #PresosPorQue ❤️🇺🇸⌛️🇳🇮🙏🏼☮️

May be an image of 2 people, people standing, book, indoor and text that says 'way Local Van Late also PLAYBILL ÛUS AUGUS WILSON THEATRE PASS'.

node.text: Holy shit. There’s nothing like a great night at the theater to buoy your spirits. Tonight I got to see “Pass Over” at the August Wilson Theatre on Broadway. My oldest and best friend @wilsonchindesign designed the set and it’s a stunner. As is the gorgeous play written by @anwandu, flawlessly directed by @danyataymor, and beautifully performed by @jonhillm, Namir Smallwood, and Gabriel Ebert. Three mega-star turns. The entire audience walked out of the theater and into a torrential rain storm on a high. If you can make it, GO SEE @passoverbway. A truly special show. (Also, Marcus Doshi’s lights, Sarafinia Bush’s costumes, and Justin Ellington’s sound design are perfection.) Thanks for a stellar night, Wilson!!! 🎭🏆🔥⚡️⭐️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Roberto Aguirre-Sacasa on August 20, 2021 tagging @gsacasa, @marcorubiofla, @senatormenendez, @cicr_mx, and @potus. May be an image of 17 people and text.

node.text: It’s actually been 24 days since my father was kidnapped. And these are only SOME of the men and women who have been arrested and disappeared by Dictator Ortega. In those 24 days, we’ve had no contact with my dad. No confirmation even that he’s in the notorious prison El Chipote (though we strongly believe he’s there). My father’s not a frail man, but he’s 76. He takes many daily medications. Despite our best efforts, every indication is that he’s NOT getting them regularly, if at all. Same with food. Same with water. Meanwhile, in the streets of Nicaragua, there’s growing unrest and violence. More illegal arrests are happening every day. Managua’s free newspaper, La Prensa, was raided and shut down. The situation in Nicaragua is dire and getting worse. Pray for the prisoners and for freedom in Nicaragua. Share their stories to help get them liberated. #freefrancisco #sosnicaragua #PresosPoliticos #PresosPorQue 🙏🔑🇺🇸🏠🔙🇳🇮

node.text: And then there were five. Our quintet of Pretty Little Liars (aka Stunning Empowered Final Girls) is complete! Welcome @maliapyles (playing Minnie) and @zariazariazaria (playing Faran) to Millwood! Can’t wait to join you in our bubble of thrills and chills! Now the only iconic character missing is…🅰️ #plloriginalsin #HBOMax 💋💃🏽🔥💥☠️🩸💣🌪🔪🪓🔫💊🔑☠️

node.text: @instasuelos sent me this picture of him and his son @michael.consuelos while shooting tonight’s episode of #Riverdale, beautifully written by @brianepaterson and spectacularly shot by @jamesdewille. It’s a special episode for so many reasons, not the least because it allowed these two handsome fellas to appear in scenes together as father and son. Made the story resonate at such a deep, emotional level. Grateful to them both. ❤️⭐️👞🍷🔫🐴💥👀💵☠️

node.text: There’s a brand-new #Riverdale tonight. But even MORE important, it’s @madelame birthday today! So outrageously talented and beautiful, she’s literally heart-stopping. Feeling INCREDIBLY grateful to have her on the show and in my life. Have a great day, Lady, love you!!! 🎁❤️⭐️🔥🕷🍒💣⚰️

node.text: How is it that @melton can somehow make eating Pop Tarts and reading comic books sexy? And yet, he does… I ❤️ tomorrow’s episode, not just because it focuses on Hiram, but because it also gives Reggie Mantle the spotlight. Beautiful work from Charles and our other leading men in this hour of television, @instasuelos and @michael.consuelos. A special #Riverdale about fathers and sons. Hits home in a lot of ways. ❤️👞🐴🔫🍷👀🔥☠️
